So, I tested this by creating a custom streamable guardrail plugin. Here is the plugin code for reference.

```
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace Drupal\ai\Plugin\AiGuardrail;

use Drupal\ai\Attribute\AiGuardrail;
use Drupal\ai\Guardrail\AiGuardrailPluginBase;
use Drupal\ai\Guardrail\Result\GuardrailResultInterface;
use Drupal\ai\Guardrail\Result\PassResult;
use Drupal\ai\Guardrail\Result\RewriteOutputResult;
use Drupal\ai\Guardrail\StreamableGuardrailInterface;
use Drupal\ai\OperationType\InputInterface;
use Drupal\ai\OperationType\OutputInterface;
use Drupal\Component\Plugin\ConfigurableInterface;
use Drupal\Core\Form\FormStateInterface;
use Drupal\Core\Plugin\PluginFormInterface;
use Drupal\Core\StringTranslation\StringTranslationTrait;
use Drupal\Core\StringTranslation\TranslatableMarkup;

#[AiGuardrail(
  id: 'block_drug_names',
  label: new TranslatableMarkup('Block Drug Names'),
  description: new TranslatableMarkup(
    'Blocks blacklisted drug names from streaming responses by replacing them with [REDACTED].'
  ),
)]
class BlockDrugNames extends AiGuardrailPluginBase implements ConfigurableInterface, PluginFormInterface, StreamableGuardrailInterface {

  use StringTranslationTrait;

  protected const DEFAULT_BLACKLIST = ['Aspirin', 'Ibuprofen', 'Paracetamol'];

  protected const REDACTED = '[REDACTED_BRAND_NAME]';

  public function defaultConfiguration(): array {
    return [
      'drug_names' => implode(', ', self::DEFAULT_BLACKLIST),
    ];
  }

  public function getConfiguration(): array {
    return $this->configuration;
  }

  public function setConfiguration(array $configuration): void {
    $this->configuration = $configuration + $this->defaultConfiguration();
  }

  public function buildConfigurationForm(array $form, FormStateInterface $form_state): array {
    $form['drug_names'] = [
      '#type' => 'textfield',
      '#title' => $this->t('Drug names to block'),
      '#description' => $this->t('Comma-separated list of drug names to redact from streaming responses (case-insensitive).'),
      '#default_value' => $this->configuration['drug_names'] ?? implode(', ', self::DEFAULT_BLACKLIST),
      '#required' => TRUE,
    ];

    return $form;
  }

  public function validateConfigurationForm(array &$form, FormStateInterface $form_state): void {
  }

  public function submitConfigurationForm(array &$form, FormStateInterface $form_state): void {
    $this->setConfiguration($form_state->getValues());
  }

  public function getStartRegex(): string {
    return '';
  }

  public function getStopRegex(): string {
    return '';
  }

  public function processStreamedBuffer(string $text): GuardrailResultInterface {
    $blacklist = $this->getBlacklist();
    $redacted = $text;

    foreach ($blacklist as $drug) {
      $drug = trim($drug);
      if ($drug === '') {
        continue;
      }
      $pattern = '/\b' . preg_quote($drug, '/') . '\b/iu';
      $redacted = preg_replace($pattern, self::REDACTED, $redacted);
    }

    if ($redacted !== $text) {
      return new RewriteOutputResult($redacted, $this);
    }

    return new PassResult($text, $this);
  }

  public function processInput(InputInterface $input): GuardrailResultInterface {
    return new PassResult('Streaming guardrail only.', $this);
  }

  public function processOutput(OutputInterface $output): GuardrailResultInterface {
    return new PassResult('Streaming guardrail only.', $this);
  }

  private function getBlacklist(): array {
    $raw = $this->configuration['drug_names'] ?? implode(', ', self::DEFAULT_BLACKLIST);
    return array_filter(array_map('trim', explode(',', $raw)));
  }

}
```

It checks if the stream contains drug names like ['Aspirin', 'Ibuprofen', 'Paracetamol'], and if found, replaces them with the text '[REDACTED_BRAND_NAME]'

Then created a Guardrail and Guardrail set (Post generate) based on this Guardrail.

**Case - 1 : The new plugin sets both getStartRegex and getStopRegex as empty ('').**
- Output does not stream at all even if it doesn't contain any blocked words. This is due to the higher buffer size set (protected int $maxGuardrailBufferSize = 8192;). Prompts used: _Write a guide on drupal, Write a guide on treating headaches at home_(The drug names get properly redacted)

**Case - 2: The new plugin sets getStartRegex as '', but sets getStopRegex as `/[a-z]\.\s+/i` (End of a sentence)**
- Streams sentence by sentence.


**Case - 3: The new plugin sets getStartRegex as '/\.\s+[A-Z]/' (Start of a sentence dot + space + Uppercase letter) and getStopRegex as `/[a-z]\.\s+/i`**
- The sentences that are matched by the start regex gets removed from the output (This seems like a bug)


I am not entirely sure if the above is the expected behavior.

